      • isConnected

        public boolean isConnected(PVAChannelHandler channel)
        Description copied from class: MultiplexedChannelHandler
        Determines from the payload whether the channel is connected or not.

        By default, this uses the usage counter to determine whether it's connected or not. One should override this to use the actual connection payload to check whether the actual protocol connection has been established.

        Overrides:
        isConnected in class MultiplexedChannelHandler<PVAChannelHandler,org.epics.pvdata.pv.PVStructure>
        Parameters:
        channel - the connection payload
        Returns:
        true if connected

      • isWriteConnected

        protected boolean isWriteConnected(PVAChannelHandler channel)
        Description copied from class: MultiplexedChannelHandler
        Determines from the payload whether the channel can be written to.

        By default, this always return false. One should override this if it's implementing a write-able data source.

        Overrides:
        isWriteConnected in class MultiplexedChannelHandler<PVAChannelHandler,org.epics.pvdata.pv.PVStructure>
        Parameters:
        channel - connection payload; not null
        Returns:
        true if ready for writes

        Description copied from class: MultiplexedChannelHandler
